In[9]:
def clean_text(text):
    text=str(text).lower()   #   
    text=re.sub('[%s]'%re.escape(string.punctuation),'',text)  #  
    text=re.sub('\n','',text)  #  
    text=re.sub('\w*\d\w*','',text) #  - ..12iphone
    text=re.sub(r'http\S+|www\S+|https\S+', '', text)#  urls
    text=re.sub(r'\S+@\S+', '', text)  # emails
    return text

stop_words=stopwords.words('english')

def remove_stopwords(text):
     #         stop_words    .
    text=' '.join(word for word in text.split(' ') if word not in stop_words) 
    return text

stemmer=nltk.SnowballStemmer('english')
def stemm_text(text):
    text=' '.join(stemmer.stem(word) for word in text.split(' '))
    return text

def embed(corpus):
    return tokenizer.texts_to_sequences(corpus) #      ID    word_index.

#''     tokens ,         tokens.
longest_train=max(texts,key=lambda sentence:len(word_tokenize(sentence)))

##         .
length_long_sentence=len(word_tokenize(longest_train))

train_padded_sequences=pad_sequences(


    embed(texts),
    length_long_sentence,
    padding='post' #padding      
)

In[20]:
embeddings_dictionary=dict() 

embedding_dim=100 #   100d  100    .
path_to_glove = 'glove.6B.100d.txt' #   GLOVE

with open(path_to_glove, encoding='utf-8') as fp:
    for line in fp: #  
        records = line.split() #     
        word = records[0] #    100   
        vector_dimensions = np.asarray(records[1:], dtype='float32') #         
        embeddings_dictionary[word] = vector_dimensions #       .

matrix GLOVE (word_index). (embedding_matrix) ID (word_index), embeddings_dictionary GLOVE ID 100d.

In[21]:
embedding_matrix=np.zeros((vocab_length,embedding_dim)) 
for word,index in tokenizer.word_index.items():  #    -ID   word_index
    embedding_vector=embeddings_dictionary.get(word) #   100d   
    if embedding_vector is not None: #     GLOVE
        embedding_matrix[index]=embedding_vector #         ID.

3)GlobalMaxPool1D &BatchNormalization: LSTM layer .

In[23]:
def glove_lstm():
 
    model=Sequential()
    #FIRST LAYER
    model.add(Embedding(
        input_dim=embedding_matrix.shape[0],#    embedding_matrix (61.881)
        output_dim=embedding_matrix.shape[1],#   (100d) 
        weights=[embedding_matrix],#     embedding_matrix
        ))
   #SECOND LAYER        
    model.add(Bidirectional(LSTM(
        length_long_sentence,#       
        return_sequences=True,
        recurrent_dropout=0.2 # 20%     
        )))
    model.add(GlobalMaxPool1D())
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Dense(length_long_sentence,activation="relu"))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Dense(length_long_sentence,activation="relu"))        

    model.add(Dense(10,activation='softmax')) #
    model.compile(loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', optimizer='adam', metrics=['accuracy'])

    return model
model=glove_lstm()
model.build(input_shape=(None, length_long_sentence))
model.summary()

model=glove_lstm()

weights = class_weight.compute_class_weight('balanced', 
                                            classes=np.unique(y_train),

    'model.h5',
    monitor='val_loss',
    verbose=1,
    save_best_only=True
)

    monitor = 'val_loss', 
    factor = 0.2,

    patience = 5,                        
    min_lr = 0.001
)

#

    X_train,

    batch_size=32,
    validation_data=(X_test,y_test), # 
    class_weight=dict_weights,
verbose=1,
callbacks=[reduce_lr,checkpoint]
)

In[25]:
def plot_learning_curves(history,arr):
    fig,ax=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(20,5))
    for idx in range(2): # loop   
        ax[idx].plot(history.history[arr[idx][0]])
        ax[idx].plot(history.history[arr[idx][1]])
        ax[idx].legend([arr[idx][0],arr[idx][1]],fontsize=18)
        ax[idx].set_xlabel('A ',fontsize=16)
        ax[idx].set_ylabel('B',fontsize=16)
        ax[idx].set_title(arr[idx][0] + ' X ' + arr[idx][1],fontsize=16)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

def conf_matrix(matrix,category_names):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    sns.heatmap(matrix, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues',xticklabels=category_names,yticklabels=category_names) 
    plt.xlabel('Predicted Label', fontsize=14)
    plt.ylabel('True Label', fontsize=14)
    plt.title('Confusion Matrix', fontsize=16)
    plt.show()

def show_metrics(y_pred,y_true):
    print(f"Accuracy Score:{accuracy_score(y_true,y_pred):.3f}")
    print("\nClassification Report:")
    print(classification_report(y_true,y_pred,target_names=names))
